From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Fennec Authors <patches@fennec.computer>
Date: Mon, 08 Apr 2024 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ui: SetupPageHandler — Mojo bridge for fennec://setup

Implements the C++ side of the fennec://setup WebUI page:

  1. SetupPageHandler (WebUIMessageHandler) — receives the commit()
     message from the React frontend when the user clicks "Start browsing",
     writes the chosen preferences to the profile, sets
     kFennecOnboardingComplete = true, and calls
     fennec::ReleaseConsentGuard() to permit outbound network traffic.

  2. Preference registration — adds the following prefs to
     chrome/browser/prefs/browser_prefs.cc:
       fennec.onboarding.complete          (bool, default false)
       fennec.services.enable_updates      (bool, default false)
       fennec.services.enable_filter_refresh (bool, default false)
       fennec.services.enable_mods_registry  (bool, default false)
       fennec.services.enable_cws_proxy      (bool, default false)

  3. Consent gate enforcement — NetworkServiceImpl::CreateURLLoaderFactory
     checks fennec.onboarding.complete via the active profile's PrefService
     before allowing any outbound HTTP/HTTPS request.  If the pref is false,
     the request is rejected with ERR_BLOCKED_BY_CLIENT and a Journal entry
     is written with:
       resource_class: kBlocked
       block_reason:   "consent-guard: setup not complete"

  4. First-launch detection — on browser startup, if
     fennec.onboarding.complete is false, the profile is redirected to
     fennec://setup before the first navigation.  This happens in
     Browser::OnFirstActiveTabCreated().

PILLAR: Privacy (enforces consent gate), Transparency (releases guard)
JOURNAL: Logs kFennecInternal events:
           "consent-guard-active"   — on guard installation
           "consent-guard-released" — on setup completion

